<%= content_tag( 'h2', 'Completing and verifying winning candidate data for new elections' ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "When new General Elections happen, the House of Commons Library ensures data accuracy by following a two-step process for the data gathering on the night of the election: ‘completing’ followed by ‘verifying’." ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "The first step is to input an accurate and complete list of winners into our database on the night of the election using a team of volunteers. The database is pre-filled with the candidates standing for each constituency prior to election night. The volunteers then identify the winning candidate for their set of constituencies, which are divided by region. Each volunteer uses two independent sources to find the data (BBC, Financial Times, or Press Association) and then marks the winning candidate as ‘winner’ in our database." ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "The second step is then to verify the data which had been inputted. Each volunteer is allocated a different region to ‘verify’ results for. The individual checks that the candidate marked as the winner is correct – using two of the same aforementioned sources. This provides us with basic data on the winning candidates." ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'h2', 'Completing and verifying all election result data for new elections' ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "Following completion of winning candidate data on the night of the election, the Library begins the process of verifying all election results data. This includes figures for results (for all candidates), turnout, invalid ballots, and total electorate. We aim to complete this within a week of the election." ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "The team uses official data from local authorities to complete this next step of the process. This data is obtained from declaration forms, local authority websites, or returning officers. In some cases it can be necessary to contact the local council to track down missing information." ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "Information is then inputted into the database with a source. A PDF or screenshot of the results is also saved into an internally stored ‘declarations’ folder in case the original source becomes unavailable in future." ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "We then verify this data; with individuals again assigned a different region to the one which they originally completed the dataset for and checking that the values match up to the sources." ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "If we are unable to find or verify a source, this is listed as ‘blocked’ until at least two sources (usually the BBC and Financial Times) match up." ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'h2', 'Verifying historic election results' ) %>

<%= content_tag( 'p', "Results for historic elections have been compiled from local authority websites, or direct communication with local authorities. In a small number of cases, we have not been able to identify the number of missing ballots. In these cases, the relevant local authorities have confirmed to us in writing that they no longer hold this information." ) %>


 
 

 





 
